<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811f.812/589b.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">
                            <hi rend="italic">To the Diplomatic Officers of the United
                            States</hi>.</p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: You are instructed to communicate
                            to the Governments to which you are respectively accredited the
                            following information relative to the opening of the Panama Canal, which
                            has been furnished by the Secretary of War: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The Panama Canal will be opened for commerce to vessels not
                                    needing more than 30 feet of water, on and after August 15,
                                    1914.</p>
                                <p>The official opening of the canal, as heretofore announced, will
                                    be in the month of March, 1915. An appropriate announcement will
                                    be made when a greater depth of water than 30 feet has been
                                    secured.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>